ActTerritorial Lands Act
SubjectWithdrawal from Disposal of Certain Tracts of Territorial Lands in Nunavut (Northern Bathurst Island National Park) Order
PrecisWITHDRAWAL FROM DISPOSAL OF CERTAIN TRACTS OF TERRITORIAL LANDS IN NUNAVUT (NORTHERN BATHURST ISLAND NATIONAL PARK) ORDER - which provides for (a) the withdrawal from disposal of some 11,800 square kilometres of land to facilitate the establishment of a Special Management Area for the protection of the Peary Caribou Population and the proposed Northern Bathurst Island National Park in Nunavut; and (b) the repeal of a similar Withdrawal from Disposal Order made in 2004.
